<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="open">Opening all or one</h3>
<p>Accordion does not control its Details children, your app does. You can allow all of the Accordion's Details to be open (the default behavior) or only one at a time. This is as simple as removing the <code>open</code> attribute from all Details children except the one the user clicked. Listen to the toggle event and check <code>e.target.open</code> to know if the toggled Details was opened or closed.</p>
<code-sample>
  <script>
    // Accordion delegated "toggle" event handler
    const handleToggle = e => e.currentTarget.querySelectorAll('details').forEach(details => details.open = details === e.target ? e.target.open : false)
  </script>
  <template>
    <m-accordion ontoggle="handleToggle(event)">
      <details id="a">
        <summary>Summary</summary>
        <p>Details about this thing</p>
      </details>
      <details id="b">
        <summary>Summary</summary>
        <p>Details about this thing</p>
      </details>
    </m-accordion>
  </template>
</code-sample>
